VEX Robotics Software Privacy Policy
Effective date: September 28, 2020
Innovation First International, Inc. ("IFI") or ("us", "we", or "our") develops and distributes the VEXcode software packages ("Applications") including VEXcode 123, VEXcode GO, VEXcode IQ, VEXcode EXP, VEXcode V5, VEXcode CTE, VEXcode AIM, VEXcode AIR, VEXcode Pro V5, VEXcode VR, the VEX VSCode Extension, VEX Classroom mobile application, and the VEX Pilot mobile application.
This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal data when you use our Applications and the choices you have associated with that data.
Applications Privacy Policy
We do not collect personally identifiable information when using our Applications aside from data submitted to us via the Feedback tool. If you wish to not provide personally identifiable information, please do not provide personally identifiable information when using the Feedback tool or please do not use the Feedback tool.
Children's Privacy
We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from anyone under the age of 18. If you are a parent or guardian and you are aware that your child has provided us with Personal Data, please contact us. If we become aware that we have collected Personal Data from children without verification of parental consent, we take steps to remove that information from our servers.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time.
You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted on this page.
Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us by e-mail:
legal@innovationfirst.com
